  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN194.1-kilavi">paruvaṅ kaṇṭu <app><lem>āṟṟāḷāy</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #C9v #RK">āṟṟāmai mītūrat</rdg></app> talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said when being unable to bear it upon seeing the season.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN194.1">
        <l>pēruṟai talaiip<anchor n="1"/> perumpular vaikaṟai</l>
        <l>yēriṭam paṭutta virumaṟup pūḻip</l>
        <l>puṟamāṟu peṟṟa pūva <supplied>lī</supplied>rat</l>
        <l>tūṉkaḻit taṉṉa ceñcuvar neṭuñcāl</l>
        <l>vittiya maruṅkiṉ vitaipala nāṟi</l>
        <l>yiralai naṉmā ṉiṉamparan tavaipōṟ</l>
        <l>kōṭuṭait talaik<supplied>ku</supplied>ṭai cūṭiya viṉaiñar</l>
        <l>kaṟaṅkupaṟaic cīri ṉiṟaṅka vāṅkik</l>
        <l>kaḷaikāl kaḻīiya perumpuṉa varakiṉ</l>
        <l>kavaikkati rirum<supplied>pu</supplied>ṟaṅ<anchor n="2"/> katūu vuṇṭa</l>
        <l>kuṭumi neṟṟi neṭumāt tōkai</l>
        <l>kāmar kalavam parappi yēmuṟak</l>
        <l>kollai yuḻavar kūḻniḻa loḻitta</l>
        <l>vallilaik kuruntiṉ vāṅkuciṉai yiruntu</l>
        <l>kiḷikaṭi makaḷiriṉ viḷipaṭap payiruṅ</l>
        <l>kārma ṉikuḷai tōḻi pōrmikak</l>
        <l>koṭuñci neṭuntēr pūṇṭa kaṭumpari</l>
        <l>viriyuḷai naṉmā <supplied>ka</supplied>ṭaii</l>
        <l>varutu meṉṟa<supplied>var</supplied> teḷitta pōḻtē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>It [is] the rainy season indeed, friend, [my] friend, (16a-c)</l>
        <l>when they call out, so that shouts fall like from women chasing parakeets, (15)</l>
        <l>perched on the bent branches of the lime tree with strong leaves (14)</l>
        <l>that is rejected as a shade for the food by the ploughmen in the clearing, (13)</l>
        <l>delightfully spreading out [their] desirable feathers, (12)</l>
        <l>the long dark peacocks with crested foreheads (11)</l>
        <l>that had seized [and] eaten the big backs of forked ears (10)</l>
        <l>on the millet in the vast field from which the [old] stalks had been removed by weeding, (9)</l>
        <l>the workmen who wore baskets on [their] bowed(?) heads (7)</l>
        <l>pulling [at them], so that they come down to the tune of sounding drums, (8)</l>
        <l>resembling a group of fine Iralai stags that is scattered, (6)</l>
        <l>smelling of the many seeds on the side that were sown (5)</l>
        <l>in the long furrow with a wall red like removed meat, (4)</l>
        <l>in the wetness of the red earth that had undergone a great transformation (3)</l>
        <l>from the dark stained dust brought under control by the plough, (2)</l>
        <l>at great dawning dawn, after big drops [of rain] had showered [it], (1)</l>
        <l>– the time he specified, saying “we will come [back], (19)</l>
        <l>urging the good horses with broad manes (18)</l>
        <l>[and] fast gait yoked to the long chariot with a [support] staff, in the thick of battle(?). (16df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

